parts: Create a high-level system architecture diagram for an application called ContractorLens. ContractorLens is a multi-platform application designed for construction contractors to generate instant, accurate estimates using augmented reality (AR) and artificial intelligence (AI). The diagram should clearly show the relationship and data flow between the following major components: a native iOS Mobile App, a Web Application, and a Backend API (deployed on Cloud Run). Indicate that the mobile app uses augmented reality using RoomPlan, while all processing and storage is done on the backend. Highlight that all components need to securely transfer data between each other. Use boxes for components and arrows for data flows. Label all parts of the diagram with descriptive names, and make the connections between components obvious.

Here is the high-level system architecture diagram for ContractorLens:

![View Diagram](https://mlai.lucid.app/plugin/images/aiplugin_55148168-0be8-4318-a35b-100fced3c249)

### Key Components and Data Flow:
1. **iOS Mobile App**: Utilizes RoomPlan for augmented reality (AR) to generate AR data.
2. **RoomPlan**: Integrated in the iOS app for AR data generation.
3. **Backend API (Cloud Run)**: Processes AR data using AI, handles secure data transmission, and stores results in cloud storage.
4. **Cloud Storage**: Stores processed data and estimates securely.
5. **Web Application**: Allows users to fetch processed estimates via the Backend API.
6. **Secure Communication**: All data transfers between components are secure.

This diagram shows the interaction and data flow among all major components. Let me know if you need further refinements!

parts:
Here is the detailed deployment diagram for the ContractorLens application's backend on Google Cloud Platform:

![View Diagram](https://mlai.lucid.app/plugin/images/aiplugin_2f2b753c-0a6d-4448-b18b-0e7ffba72368)

You can also [edit this diagram in Lucidchart](https://mlai.lucid.app/plugin/edit/aiplugin_2f2b753c-0a6d-4448-b18b-0e7ffba72368) for further customization.

### Key Components and Interactions:
1. **Backend API (Cloud Run)**:
   - Central component that orchestrates requests and handles API calls.
   - Secures credentials via **Google Secret Manager**.
   - Communicates with all other services.
2. **Google Secret Manager**:
   - Safeguards sensitive keys, tokens, and credentials.
   - Provides secure access to the Backend API.
3. **Firestore**:
   - Persistent storage for application data, such as user profiles and session data.
4. **Vertex AI**:
   - Processes data to generate AI-powered estimates.
5. **Gemini API**:
   - Enhances augmented reality with object detection and semantic understanding from real-time video feeds.
6. **Cloud Storage**:
   - Stores large data objects like AR-generated files and video streams.
7. **BigQuery**:
   - Enables robust data warehousing and analytics for reporting and deeper insights.

### Data Flow:
- The **Backend API** uses credentials from **Secret Manager** to securely connect with all services.
- Data from AR processing is sent to **Cloud Storage**, while semantic insights are enhanced via **Gemini API**.
- AI estimates are computed through **Vertex AI**, and user-related data is managed in **Firestore**.
- All logs and analytical data are aggregated in **BigQuery** for insights and reporting.

Let me know if further details or adjustments are needed!

parts: Create a data flow diagram that illustrates the journey of data across the entire ContractorLens application. Start with the iOS mobile app performing an AR scan using the RoomPlan API, and collecting spatial data and a real time video, show how this data is then sent to the Gemini API for object detection, and semantic understanding, to the backend API to generate a dynamic prompt, then on to Vertex AI to generate the estimate. Finally show how the resulting estimate is sent back to both the iOS mobile app and web application. The diagram should also show all error flows, and how the application should behave if there are errors using secure communication protocols to make sure that all data is safe. Also highlight data transformations that occur at each step, and specific details on the data that is being passed.

content.text:
{"validDiagramCode": "flowchart TD
  IOSApp["iOS Mobile App"]
  RoomPlan["RoomPlan API (AR Scan & Spatial Data)"]
  VideoData["Real-Time Video"]
  SpatialData["Spatial Data"]
  GeminiAPI["Gemini API (Object Detection & Semantic Understanding)"]
  BackendAPI["Backend API"]
  DynamicPrompt["Dynamic Prompt"]
  VertexAI["Vertex AI (Generate Estimate)"]
  EstimateData["Generated Estimate"]
  WebApp["Web Application"]

  subgraph Data Capture
    IOSApp -->|"Performs AR Scan"| RoomPlan
    RoomPlan -->|"Outputs Spatial Data"| SpatialData
    IOSApp -->|"Captures Real-Time Video"| VideoData
  end

  subgraph Processing Flow
    SpatialData -->|"Sent to Backend API via Secure Protocol"| BackendAPI
    VideoData -->|"Sent to Gemini API via Secure Protocol"| GeminiAPI
    GeminiAPI -->|"Generates Semantic Understanding"| BackendAPI
    BackendAPI -->|"Transforms Data into Dynamic Prompt"| DynamicPrompt
    DynamicPrompt -->|"Sent to Vertex AI"| VertexAI
    VertexAI -->|"Processes Prompt to Generate Estimate"| EstimateData
  end

  subgraph Result Delivery
    EstimateData -->|"Sent Back to iOS App"| IOSApp
    EstimateData -->|"Sent to Web App via Secure Protocol"| WebApp
  end

  subgraph Error Handling
    GeminiAPI -->|"Error Response"| BackendAPI
    BackendAPI -->|"Logs Error & Sends Notification to iOS App"| IOSApp
    BackendAPI -->|"Logs Error & Sends Notification to Web App"| WebApp
  end

  subgraph Data Transformation
    SpatialData -->|"Processed to Identify Key Features"| BackendAPI
    VideoData -->|"Transformed to Semantic Context"| BackendAPI
    DynamicPrompt -->|"Converted into AI-Readable Format"| VertexAI
    EstimateData -->|"Formatted for UI"| IOSApp & WebApp
  end"}

parts:
Here is the data flow diagram illustrating the journey of data across the ContractorLens application:

![View Diagram](https://mlai.lucid.app/plugin/images/aiplugin_4319fbbb-2bf6-4628-a581-5f04762f3412)

You can also [edit this diagram in Lucidchart](https://mlai.lucid.app/plugin/edit/aiplugin_4319fbbb-2bf6-4628-a581-5f04762f3412) for further customization.

### Data Flow Details:
1. **Data Capture**:
   - The **iOS Mobile App** initiates an AR scan using **RoomPlan**, collecting spatial data.
   - Simultaneously, real-time video is captured and prepared for processing.
2. **Processing Flow**:
   - **Spatial Data** is securely transmitted to the **Backend API**, where key features are extracted.
   - Real-time video is sent to **Gemini API** for object detection and semantic understanding, which then informs the **Backend API**.
   - The **Backend API** transforms all input into a **Dynamic Prompt**, formatted for AI processing.
   - The **Dynamic Prompt** is sent to **Vertex AI**, which generates the **Estimate**.
3. **Result Delivery**:
   - The generated **Estimate** is securely sent back to both the **iOS Mobile App** and the **Web Application**.
4. **Error Handling**:
   - If the **Gemini API** or any component encounters an error, the **Backend API** logs the issue and notifies the **iOS Mobile App** and **Web Application**.
   - Errors are transmitted using secure protocols to maintain data integrity.
5. **Data Transformation**:
   - Spatial data is processed to extract actionable features.
   - Video data is converted into semantic context.
   - The **Dynamic Prompt** is formatted into an AI-readable structure for **Vertex AI**.
   - The final **Estimate** is tailored for display in user interfaces.

This diagram ensures comprehensive understanding of data flow, transformations, and error handling across the system. Let me know if further refinements are required!
